## CRUD Passwords [/passwords]

Retrieve or update passwords.

### CRUD Passwords [POST]

This endpoint uses two types of weak challenge / response authentication. 

1) Every 5-10 seconds a challenge token is deleted on the server. A new one is generated when the client POSTs to /passwords.
2) Additionally, if a user's IP address is know in the list of known IPs then the user is required to answer a question which they have set (e.g. 'what is the name of your pet?')

For each of these authentication protocols, there is a set number of max retries, after which the accout will be locked.

+ challengeResponse (string) - Response to challenge authentication. See [Service Overview](index.html) for more information.
+ answerResponse(string) - Response to question and answer authentication
+ newPasswords(string) - new encrypted JSON to store as passwords

+ Request Initial Request (application/json)
        
    {
      "newPasswords" : "slkdjf]-93jfpijs'dfija'jefw;oeuhwaehjshdg"
    }


